<paragraph blockId="14.[189,1236,1963,2025]" box="[189,1236,1998,2025]" pageId="14" pageNumber="94">MEASUREMENTS. Body length (without ovipositor) 4.0 mm. Fore wing about 3.0 mm long.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="95" startId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" targetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" targetPageId="15">
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,1399,1892,2025]" pageId="15" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,271,1892,1919]" pageId="15" pageNumber="95">Fig. 7.</emphasis>
Morphology of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bordera" authorityName="Bordera" authorityYear="2021" box="[479,863,1893,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Handaoia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruizcancinoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[479,757,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="95">Handaoia ruizcancinoi</emphasis>
Bordera
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[874,971,1893,1919]" pageId="15" pageNumber="95" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype, ♀ (CEUA). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1260,1281,1892,1918]" pageId="15" pageNumber="95">A</emphasis>
. Habitus, lateral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[343,361,1928,1954]" pageId="15" pageNumber="95">B</emphasis>
. Head, front view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[587,608,1928,1954]" pageId="15" pageNumber="95">C</emphasis>
. Head and mososoma, lateral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1032,1053,1928,1954]" pageId="15" pageNumber="95">D</emphasis>
. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[260,280,1963,1989]" pageId="15" pageNumber="95">E</emphasis>
. Tergite I, dorsal view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[564,581,1963,1989]" pageId="15" pageNumber="95">F</emphasis>
. Metasoma, dorsal view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[888,909,1963,1989]" pageId="15" pageNumber="95">G</emphasis>
. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[190,211,1998,2024]" pageId="15" pageNumber="95">H</emphasis>
. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,265,573]" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">
HEAD. Finely granulate, matt, strongly narrowed behind eyes, occiput very concave centrally in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[266,397,300,327]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7B–D</figureCitation>
); gena 0.14 × length of eye in dorsal view; posterior ocellus separated from eye by 1.55 × its maximum diameter; distance between posterior ocelli 1.27 × maximum ocellar diameter; occipital carina gently V-shaped medially (
<figureCitation box="[704,800,370,397]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
); malar space 1.3× basal width of mandible; face conspicuously swollen medially (
<figureCitation box="[600,699,406,432]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
); clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[840,936,406,432]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
) quite convex, gently granulate with scattered coarse punctures, apex slightly rounded, about 1.8 × as wide as high; mandible quite tapered to apex, ventral tooth of mandible a little shorter than upper tooth; flagellum widened in middle, tapered towards apex, flagellomeres 8–18 flattened ventrally; flagellum with 20 segments, length-thickness ratios: 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[284,295,546,560]" fontSize="6" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">st</superScript>
segment = 4.1, 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[498,515,546,560]" fontSize="6" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">nd</superScript>
= 3.27 and 10 
<superScript attach="left" box="[684,697,546,560]" fontSize="6" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">th</superScript>
= 0.72.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[188,1400,612,991]" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">
MESOSOMA. Finely granulate and matt (
<figureCitation box="[685,867,612,638]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7A, C–D</figureCitation>
); mesoscutum slightly convex, almost flat posteriorly; notauli moderately deep over 0.7× length of mesoscutum (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1122,647,674]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
); scutellum moderately convex, without lateral carinae; sternaulus as a wide V-shaped depression anteriorly, reaching about 0.3× the length of mesopleuron (
<figureCitation box="[574,666,718,744]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
); juxtacoxal carina weak but complete, joining submetapleural carina at its anterior part (
<figureCitation box="[501,596,753,779]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7G</figureCitation>
, arrow); propodeum (
<figureCitation box="[857,952,753,779]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1891,1917]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,400,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-46@4.[189,1398,400,1853]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Propodeum and tergite I of Handaoia spp., ♀♀. A. H. cuscoensis Bordera sp. nov., holotype (AEIC).B. H. fritzi sp. nov., holotype (NHMUK).C. H. mercedensisBordera sp. nov., holotype (CEUA). D. H. plaumanni sp. nov., holotype (NHMUK). E. H. ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype (CEUA). F. H. urceus sp. nov., holotype (NHMUK). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047685/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Figs 1E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[967,1041,753,779]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">7C, H</figureCitation>
) with strong and conspicuous carinae; area superomedia confluent with area basalis and separated from area petiolaris; inner side of area externa about 7.0× as long as inner side of area dentipara; inner side of area dentipara about 0.3× length of outer side; area spiracularis confluent with area lateralis; posterior transverse carina strong, forming an elevated apophysis joining lateral longitudinal carina, apophysis subtriangular with blunt tip (
<figureCitation box="[197,327,929,955]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7C, H</figureCitation>
, arrow). Length of hind femur 3.9× its height. Hind wing with vein 
<emphasis box="[1140,1193,930,955]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">cu-a</emphasis>
0.77 × as long as abscissa of 
<emphasis box="[324,365,964,990]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">CU</emphasis>
between 
<emphasis box="[478,502,965,990]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">M</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[560,613,965,990]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">cu-a</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1400,1029,1197]" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">
METASOMA. Tergite I (
<figureCitation box="[460,553,1029,1056]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
) finely granulate, shiny, strigose laterally, about 2.4× as long as its maximum width; lateromedian longitudinal carina moderately strong, reaching posterior 0.8× length of tergite; lateral longitudinal carina present from spiracle to posterior margin of postpetiole; tergite II (
<figureCitation box="[199,286,1135,1162]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7F</figureCitation>
) shiny, smooth and almost glabrous; remaining tergites (
<figureCitation box="[956,1044,1135,1162]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7F</figureCitation>
) smooth and shiny, with short and moderately dense setiferous punctures. Ovipositor sheath about 0.5× as long as hind tibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,1236,1403]" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">
COLOUR. Head (
<figureCitation box="[374,501,1236,1262]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7B–D</figureCitation>
) brown, darker dorsally, lighter ventrally, mandibular teeth and labrum dark brown; antenna with scape, pedicel and first flagellomere light brown, remaining flagellomeres dark brown, flagellomeres 5–7 dorsally white (
<figureCitation box="[700,800,1306,1332]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
). Mesosoma (
<figureCitation box="[971,1107,1306,1332]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7A, C</figureCitation>
) brown, more infuscate ventrally. Metasoma (
<figureCitation box="[448,569,1341,1368]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7E–F</figureCitation>
) dark brown. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[814,908,1341,1367]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
) mostly dark brown; fore and mid coxae and trochanters, and hind trochanter, white. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[798,890,1376,1403]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,322,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[189,1398,322,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Morphology of Handaoia ruizcancinoi Bordera sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (CEUA). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, front view. C. Head and mososoma, lateral view. D. Head and mososoma, dorsal view. E. Tergite I, dorsal view. F. Metasoma, dorsal view. G. Metapleuron (arrow: juxtacoxal carina). H. Propodeum (arrow: propodeal apophysis). Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 0.2 mm; G–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5047699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5047699/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
) evenly infuscate.
</paragraph>
